The paper discusses the application of deep neural network models to information retrieval, which is a core topic in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions Torch, a popular machine learning library for deep learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of a simple interface for exposing the search capabilities of Indri to Torch models, which involves programming languages and frameworks, falling under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
